1
00:00:01,040 --> 00:01:45,000
♪

2
00:01:47,270 --> 00:01:52,280
♪

3
00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:55,050
This is where you'll
fight the next duel,

4
00:01:55,050 --> 00:01:56,290
and considering
who you're fighting

5
00:01:56,290 --> 00:01:58,220
you'll never leave
this room alive.

6
00:01:58,220 --> 00:02:01,040
Spare me the
sales pitch, will ya?

7
00:02:01,040 --> 00:02:03,070
(grunts)

8
00:02:03,070 --> 00:02:04,210
Very impressive.

9
00:02:04,210 --> 00:02:07,130
Now, where's the guy
we're supposed to fight?

10
00:02:07,130 --> 00:02:09,050
Usui.

11
00:02:09,050 --> 00:02:11,040
Where are you?

12
00:02:11,040 --> 00:02:12,070
Here.

13
00:02:12,070 --> 00:02:15,010
♪

14
00:02:15,010 --> 00:02:17,010
Oh, there you are.

15
00:02:17,010 --> 00:02:18,110
Welcome, gentlemen.

16
00:02:18,110 --> 00:02:20,140
♪

17
00:02:20,140 --> 00:02:21,160
Glad you could come.

18
00:02:21,160 --> 00:02:42,140
♪

19
00:02:42,140 --> 00:02:46,180
So, which one of you
wants to die first?

20
00:02:46,180 --> 00:02:49,050
After I've killed you two,
I'll kill Shishio.

21
00:02:49,050 --> 00:02:51,250
Then use all three of
your heads as decorations.

22
00:02:51,250 --> 00:02:54,230
Usui, Shishio is the
leader of the Juupongatana.

23
00:02:54,230 --> 00:02:56,060
Just what
do you mean?

24
00:02:56,060 --> 00:02:58,210
That was the
agreement we had.

25
00:02:58,210 --> 00:03:00,280
When I joined his group,
I told Shishio

26
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:03,230
I would kill him
if I had the chance.

27
00:03:03,230 --> 00:03:04,290
(growls)

28
00:03:07,040 --> 00:03:08,270
Shishio knows that?

29
00:03:08,270 --> 00:03:10,030
Of course he does,

30
00:03:10,030 --> 00:03:11,180
but he needed a
fighter like me,

31
00:03:11,180 --> 00:03:13,070
so he agreed to it.

32
00:03:13,070 --> 00:03:15,030
He needed my skill.

33
00:03:15,030 --> 00:03:16,170
Eyes of the heart.

34
00:03:16,170 --> 00:03:17,170
Hmm?

35
00:03:17,170 --> 00:03:19,170
(gasps)

36
00:03:19,170 --> 00:03:22,080
Good for you, Ayumi,
you've made a wise decision.

37
00:03:22,080 --> 00:03:23,110
You couldn't
fight your way

38
00:03:23,110 --> 00:03:24,170
out of a wet grain sack

39
00:03:24,170 --> 00:03:26,080
with that little
blade of yours.

40
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:27,250
(chuckling)

41
00:03:34,090 --> 00:03:35,290
(groaning)

42
00:03:38,060 --> 00:03:39,100
Anji?

43
00:03:39,100 --> 00:03:40,230
So, you're awake.

44
00:03:40,230 --> 00:03:42,020
That medicine that
Kenshin left me

45
00:03:42,020 --> 00:03:45,090
is a lot stronger
than I thought.

46
00:03:45,090 --> 00:03:47,280
You took care of
me after he left?

47
00:03:47,280 --> 00:03:49,170
You're lucky that
Kenshin had this stuff.

48
00:03:49,170 --> 00:03:51,210
I think you would have
died without this.

49
00:03:51,210 --> 00:03:54,190
You've got some friends who
really care about you, Sano.

50
00:03:54,190 --> 00:03:56,100
(chuckling)

51
00:03:56,100 --> 00:03:58,270
My whole body is aching.

52
00:03:58,270 --> 00:04:00,090
But that's okay.

53
00:04:00,090 --> 00:04:02,050
I haven't had a
workout like that

54
00:04:02,050 --> 00:04:03,240
since the last time
I fought Kenshin.

55
00:04:03,240 --> 00:04:05,100
You're some piece
of work, Anji.

56
00:04:05,100 --> 00:04:08,160
Speaking of Kenshin,
where is he?

57
00:04:08,160 --> 00:04:11,100
He and Saito went to fight
the next duel with Usui.

58
00:04:11,100 --> 00:04:12,190
He's one of
Shishio's group

59
00:04:12,190 --> 00:04:13,260
left here to fight
the three of you

60
00:04:13,260 --> 00:04:15,130
while the rest
went to Aoiya.

61
00:04:15,130 --> 00:04:18,160
You mean, he sent the
Juupongatana group to Aoiya?

62
00:04:18,160 --> 00:04:22,120
You can still catch up with
Kenshin if you go right now.

63
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:24,040
The room at the
end of the hallway.

64
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:25,180
Right!

65
00:04:25,180 --> 00:04:29,100
Anji, before I go.

66
00:04:29,100 --> 00:04:30,270
I guess I
owe you one,

67
00:04:30,270 --> 00:04:32,010
but don't think
for one second

68
00:04:32,010 --> 00:04:34,080
that means I'm gonna
go easy on you.

69
00:04:34,080 --> 00:04:37,140
So, next time,
we'll have a real battle.

70
00:04:37,140 --> 00:04:39,150
I don't ever want to
have to fight you again.

71
00:04:39,150 --> 00:04:42,110
You're not a challenge,
but if I have to, I will.

72
00:04:42,110 --> 00:04:45,050
Oh yeah, well, I'm gonna
stay in training just in case,

73
00:04:45,050 --> 00:04:46,150
and I guarantee
that next time,

74
00:04:46,150 --> 00:04:47,280
I'll knock you
into next year.

75
00:04:47,280 --> 00:04:50,090
(grunts)

76
00:04:50,090 --> 00:04:51,090
(snickers)

77
00:04:51,090 --> 00:04:52,220
See ya!

78
00:04:52,220 --> 00:04:54,050
He'll never learn.

79
00:04:58,270 --> 00:05:01,100
♪

80
00:05:01,100 --> 00:05:03,200
Hmm, so.

81
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:06,110
Saito Hajime, and the
small one is Battosai.

82
00:05:06,110 --> 00:05:08,030
You're sweating and
your hearts are racing

83
00:05:08,030 --> 00:05:11,170
so I suppose you already
know about Aoiya.

84
00:05:11,170 --> 00:05:13,020
Anji must have told you.

85
00:05:13,020 --> 00:05:16,280
I knew he'd betray us
sooner or later.

86
00:05:16,280 --> 00:05:19,040
I'm really not interested
in anything you have to say.

87
00:05:19,040 --> 00:05:21,270
I didn't come here
to listen to you talk.

88
00:05:21,270 --> 00:05:23,150
Kenshin!

89
00:05:23,150 --> 00:05:25,040
Sano, hi.

90
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:26,040
You all right?

91
00:05:26,040 --> 00:05:27,280
Yeah, just fine, thanks.

92
00:05:27,280 --> 00:05:30,080
So, he's the next one
we gotta fight, right?

93
00:05:30,080 --> 00:05:31,120
Yeah.

94
00:05:31,120 --> 00:05:32,210
Anji did betray us.

95
00:05:32,210 --> 00:05:34,070
That's the only way
a fool like you

96
00:05:34,070 --> 00:05:35,260
could have survived
the first duel.

97
00:05:35,260 --> 00:05:38,200
Ah, well, I guess I'll
have to kill you too.

98
00:05:38,200 --> 00:05:40,170
You are history.

99
00:05:40,170 --> 00:05:42,000
It's all right to
fight when you're angry

100
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:43,200
as long as your anger
is under control.

101
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:45,090
Otherwise, it'll
cause muscular tension

102
00:05:45,090 --> 00:05:47,220
that inhibits
flexibility and accuracy.

103
00:05:47,220 --> 00:05:48,260
Out of the way.

104
00:05:48,260 --> 00:05:50,250
While you and Sano
are on your way to Aoiya,

105
00:05:50,250 --> 00:05:52,040
I'll be taking
care of this guy.

106
00:05:52,040 --> 00:05:54,000
-Now, go.
-You mustn't.

107
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:56,070
It's too late to
save anyone in Aoiya.

108
00:05:56,070 --> 00:05:57,250
You've got to stay
here and fight!

109
00:05:57,250 --> 00:05:59,070
Those were
Shishio's orders.

110
00:05:59,070 --> 00:06:01,000
-Go.
-Next time.

111
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:02,150
Wait, you can't go!

112
00:06:02,150 --> 00:06:04,030
-Come back!
-You're coming along too!

113
00:06:04,030 --> 00:06:05,030
I'm coming,
Kenshin.

114
00:06:05,030 --> 00:06:06,150
Put me down,
you idiot.

115
00:06:06,150 --> 00:06:08,170
I'm Shishio's lover.

116
00:06:08,170 --> 00:06:10,290
My, my, how
incredibly touching.

117
00:06:10,290 --> 00:06:12,290
One man staying
behind to die

118
00:06:12,290 --> 00:06:15,160
so that his friends can
live a few minutes longer.

119
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:16,280
What a sweet man.

120
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:18,060
(chuckling)

121
00:06:18,060 --> 00:06:21,000
Wrong, I have no intention
of dying anytime soon,

122
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:23,030
and I'm not sweet at all.

123
00:06:23,030 --> 00:06:26,230
As for Kenshin, I plan on
fighting him one day myself.

124
00:06:26,230 --> 00:06:29,060
(growls)

125
00:06:29,060 --> 00:06:31,240
So, I'm afraid I'll
just have to kill you.

126
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:33,060
Let me go, you brute.

127
00:06:33,060 --> 00:06:34,240
Put me down!

128
00:06:34,240 --> 00:06:36,050
I hate Usui.

129
00:06:36,050 --> 00:06:38,120
I want him dead
as much as you do,

130
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:42,040
but first, I want him to
kill Saito and kill you next.

131
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:44,100
But there's no way a guy
like Usui can beat Saito.

132
00:06:44,100 --> 00:06:45,100
You're wrong.

133
00:06:45,100 --> 00:06:46,260
He's a stone-cold killer.

134
00:06:46,260 --> 00:06:50,120
You should have
seen what he did at Kobe.

135
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:51,240
(screaming)

136
00:06:54,160 --> 00:06:55,260
Are you all right, boy?

137
00:06:55,260 --> 00:06:57,000
Hold it right there!

138
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:59,090
Who are you,
how'd you get in here?

139
00:06:59,090 --> 00:07:01,090
You, the third guy
from the right.

140
00:07:01,090 --> 00:07:03,180
You have a good stance and
you hold your sword well,

141
00:07:03,180 --> 00:07:05,190
so I guess you were
trained in Satsuma, right?

142
00:07:05,190 --> 00:07:07,100
And how did
you know that?

143
00:07:07,100 --> 00:07:08,100
Lucky guess.

144
00:07:08,100 --> 00:07:10,150
We'll attack him together
working as a team.

145
00:07:10,150 --> 00:07:12,210
♪

146
00:07:12,210 --> 00:07:14,160
Take four men and attack
from his left flank

147
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:16,020
when I give the signal.

148
00:07:16,020 --> 00:07:18,080
The rest of you get ready
for a simultaneous attack

149
00:07:18,080 --> 00:07:19,200
on his right flank.

150
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:22,250
So, you're going to attack me
from both sides at once, eh?

151
00:07:22,250 --> 00:07:25,030
My, what a dirty trick.

152
00:07:25,030 --> 00:07:27,070
But typical for
government work.

153
00:07:27,070 --> 00:07:28,280
Surrender or die.

154
00:07:28,280 --> 00:07:30,070
(chuckling)

155
00:07:30,070 --> 00:07:32,130
I'm afraid I can't
make the same offer.

156
00:07:32,130 --> 00:07:33,290
I'm going to kill
you and your men

157
00:07:33,290 --> 00:07:35,270
whether you
surrender or not.

158
00:07:35,270 --> 00:07:36,270
(gulps)

159
00:07:36,270 --> 00:07:38,040
Get him!

160
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:39,290
(men yelling)

161
00:07:39,290 --> 00:07:43,190
♪

162
00:07:43,190 --> 00:07:46,220
(grunting and laughing)

163
00:07:50,150 --> 00:07:53,120
(groaning)

164
00:07:53,120 --> 00:07:55,010
You're an
arrogant man, Captain,

165
00:07:55,010 --> 00:07:57,280
and because of that I'm going
to make you suffer the longest.

166
00:07:57,280 --> 00:08:00,240
Yes, a slow
and painful death.

167
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:03,050
Thank you, Captain,
it's been a pleasure.

168
00:08:06,020 --> 00:08:08,290
(laughing evilly)

169
00:08:08,290 --> 00:08:10,250
He's like a killing machine.

170
00:08:10,250 --> 00:08:12,280
(breathing heavily)

171
00:08:12,280 --> 00:08:17,030
♪

172
00:08:17,030 --> 00:08:18,190
Kill me?

173
00:08:18,190 --> 00:08:20,110
Mm-hmm.

174
00:08:20,110 --> 00:08:22,060
I suppose you're angry

175
00:08:22,060 --> 00:08:25,080
because I killed 50 of your
fellow policemen in Kobe.

176
00:08:25,080 --> 00:08:28,070
In fact, the Kobe garrison
was quite a disappointment.

177
00:08:28,070 --> 00:08:30,150
You see, I went there
because I needed practice

178
00:08:30,150 --> 00:08:32,210
and they hardly put
up any fight at all.

179
00:08:32,210 --> 00:08:34,220
Ah, I see your anger
is turning to hatred.

180
00:08:34,220 --> 00:08:36,090
Excellent.

181
00:08:36,090 --> 00:08:38,000
Not even you can
hide your feelings

182
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:39,120
from the eyes of the heart.

183
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:40,280
You feel the
need for revenge

184
00:08:40,280 --> 00:08:42,140
and that's what
I want you to feel.

185
00:08:42,140 --> 00:08:45,000
That way you'll provide
more of a challenge.

186
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:46,040
You're a fraud.

187
00:08:46,040 --> 00:08:47,040
Eyes of the heart.

188
00:08:47,040 --> 00:08:48,250
This power you have,
it isn't witchcraft.

189
00:08:48,250 --> 00:08:49,280
It isn't telepathy,

190
00:08:49,280 --> 00:08:52,200
it isn't supernatural
or magical, it's nothing.

191
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:54,220
You may be able to
know my state of mind,

192
00:08:54,220 --> 00:08:56,090
but you can't
read my thoughts.

193
00:08:56,090 --> 00:08:57,110
What?

194
00:08:57,110 --> 00:08:58,240
Protecting the
safety of Japan

195
00:08:58,240 --> 00:09:00,030
and the lives
of its citizens

196
00:09:00,030 --> 00:09:01,160
was the sworn
duty of every one

197
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:03,150
of those men you
killed in Kobe.

198
00:09:03,150 --> 00:09:04,220
Just as it is
for all of those

199
00:09:04,220 --> 00:09:07,020
who chose to become members
of the police force.

200
00:09:07,020 --> 00:09:08,250
No one compelled
them to be cops,

201
00:09:08,250 --> 00:09:10,180
and they knew that it
was a dangerous job

202
00:09:10,180 --> 00:09:13,240
that would sooner or later
put them in harms way.

203
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:16,110
This also applies to the
members of the shinsen group.

204
00:09:16,110 --> 00:09:18,000
There was no doubt
in any of our minds

205
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:20,160
that some of us would be
killed in the line of duty.

206
00:09:20,160 --> 00:09:21,210
So you're quite mistaken

207
00:09:21,210 --> 00:09:23,210
if you think that my motive
for wanting to kill you

208
00:09:23,210 --> 00:09:26,000
is for the sake of
those men to get revenge.

209
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:27,000
I'm going to kill you

210
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:28,080
because you're the
essence of evil

211
00:09:28,080 --> 00:09:31,080
and the world will be a better
place without you in it.

212
00:09:31,080 --> 00:09:32,200
I'm certain there
are a great many

213
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:34,150
who would agree with
you if they could speak,

214
00:09:34,150 --> 00:09:36,070
but unfortunately,
they're all dead.

215
00:09:36,070 --> 00:09:38,130
♪

216
00:09:38,130 --> 00:09:40,250
And now the time has come
for you to join them.

217
00:09:40,250 --> 00:09:44,050
I'm going to
shower in your blood.

218
00:09:44,050 --> 00:09:45,200
(grunting)

219
00:09:49,030 --> 00:09:53,060
I guess your great
gatotsu sword isn't so great.

220
00:10:02,270 --> 00:10:06,100
♪

221
00:10:06,100 --> 00:10:07,260
What, only three wounds?

222
00:10:07,260 --> 00:10:09,000
Surprising.

223
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:12,090
You're good, but you look
mystified and I know why.

224
00:10:12,090 --> 00:10:15,010
The gotatsu has
never failed you before.

225
00:10:15,010 --> 00:10:17,250
So, why now?

226
00:10:17,250 --> 00:10:19,050
Want to know?

227
00:10:19,050 --> 00:10:21,230
Yes, yes of course you do,
so I shall tell you.

228
00:10:21,230 --> 00:10:23,060
Like you said,
the eyes of the heart

229
00:10:23,060 --> 00:10:24,180
isn't anything
like witchcraft

230
00:10:24,180 --> 00:10:26,230
or a supernatural
or magical force.

231
00:10:26,230 --> 00:10:30,110
It has its roots
in the end of an era.

232
00:10:30,110 --> 00:10:32,290
On the day that marked the
end of the Tokugawa era,

233
00:10:32,290 --> 00:10:35,020
and the beginning of
the Meiji restoration,

234
00:10:35,020 --> 00:10:36,080
I fought against Shishio

235
00:10:36,080 --> 00:10:38,000
and I lost my eyesight.

236
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:40,160
No one had any
use for a blind fighter,

237
00:10:40,160 --> 00:10:43,140
so I was taken to the
woods and left to die.

238
00:10:43,140 --> 00:10:44,190
I couldn't see,

239
00:10:44,190 --> 00:10:46,080
had no idea where
they'd taken me,

240
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:48,170
and was in
excruciating pain.

241
00:10:48,170 --> 00:10:50,160
I knew that I wouldn't
survive much longer.

242
00:10:50,160 --> 00:10:53,050
♪

243
00:10:53,050 --> 00:10:55,010
I couldn't tell
day from night.

244
00:10:55,010 --> 00:10:57,150
I couldn't tell if
I were alive or dead.

245
00:10:57,150 --> 00:11:01,110
At times, my heart
stopped beating, and then--

246
00:11:01,110 --> 00:11:02,180
And then...

247
00:11:02,180 --> 00:11:15,090
♪

248
00:11:15,090 --> 00:11:17,070
There was a sound.

249
00:11:17,070 --> 00:11:18,170
The first sound
I'd been aware of

250
00:11:18,170 --> 00:11:21,030
in what seemed to be
a very long time.

251
00:11:21,030 --> 00:11:23,090
It was the sound
of running water.

252
00:11:23,090 --> 00:11:25,080
The sound of a stream.

253
00:11:25,080 --> 00:11:28,030
That sound made me
realize how thirsty I was.

254
00:11:28,030 --> 00:11:32,170
So, I rose, stumbled through
the woods towards the sound,

255
00:11:32,170 --> 00:11:33,260
and then I realized,

256
00:11:33,260 --> 00:11:36,230
I had heard the water
from more than a mile away.

257
00:11:36,230 --> 00:11:38,110
Even though it
was a tiny stream,

258
00:11:38,110 --> 00:11:40,120
making barely
any sound at all,

259
00:11:40,120 --> 00:11:42,190
I think it was dying and
then coming back to life

260
00:11:42,190 --> 00:11:44,280
that were the origin
of the eyes of the heart.

261
00:11:44,280 --> 00:11:46,020
Which is really
nothing more

262
00:11:46,020 --> 00:11:48,190
than having super
sensitive hearing.

263
00:11:48,190 --> 00:11:49,270
Once you have
this super hearing,

264
00:11:49,270 --> 00:11:52,080
a human is like
a lump of sound.

265
00:11:52,080 --> 00:11:55,050
Their heartbeat teaches
me their state of mind,

266
00:11:55,050 --> 00:11:56,260
and the quality of
the muscle stretch sound

267
00:11:56,260 --> 00:11:58,220
teaches me their
state of readiness

268
00:11:58,220 --> 00:12:01,090
and when they're
about to attack.

269
00:12:01,090 --> 00:12:03,080
That's the secret of
the eyes of the heart,

270
00:12:03,080 --> 00:12:04,160
and that also
explains why

271
00:12:04,160 --> 00:12:07,130
your gatotsu technique
is useless against me.

272
00:12:07,130 --> 00:12:09,020
Ah, your heart's
beating faster.

273
00:12:09,020 --> 00:12:10,190
That must have
made you angry.

274
00:12:10,190 --> 00:12:11,200
(snickers)

275
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:13,180
I knew all along that
you were a nutcase, Usui,

276
00:12:13,180 --> 00:12:15,270
but I had no idea that
you were quite so stupid.

277
00:12:15,270 --> 00:12:16,270
What?

278
00:12:16,270 --> 00:12:21,060
♪

279
00:12:21,060 --> 00:12:23,130
Thanks for
your humble story.

280
00:12:23,130 --> 00:12:24,250
To show my appreciation,

281
00:12:24,250 --> 00:12:26,030
I'll return the favor

282
00:12:26,030 --> 00:12:28,040
and tell you about
my eyes of the heart.

283
00:12:28,040 --> 00:12:29,180
Your eyes of the heart?

284
00:12:29,180 --> 00:12:33,020
♪

285
00:12:35,170 --> 00:12:37,110
♪

286
00:12:37,110 --> 00:12:40,140
Your eyes of the heart?

287
00:12:40,140 --> 00:12:42,070
My ability to
understand an opponent

288
00:12:42,070 --> 00:12:45,010
is quite different from
your super sensitive hearing.

289
00:12:45,010 --> 00:12:46,290
It's foundation
is psychological.

290
00:12:46,290 --> 00:12:50,070
Understanding the true
motivation of the enemy.

291
00:12:50,070 --> 00:12:51,160
In other words, insight

292
00:12:51,160 --> 00:12:54,240
into the needs of
another human being.

293
00:12:54,240 --> 00:12:58,120
Ah, and just what does your
heart tell you about me?

294
00:12:58,120 --> 00:13:00,040
It tells me a
great deal about you,

295
00:13:00,040 --> 00:13:03,190
including the real reason
you joined the Juupongatana.

296
00:13:03,190 --> 00:13:05,170
You said it was
to kill Shishio,

297
00:13:05,170 --> 00:13:09,050
but that's not the
real reason, is it?

298
00:13:09,050 --> 00:13:10,140
When you were
giving your speech

299
00:13:10,140 --> 00:13:12,200
about Shishio robbing
you of your eyesight

300
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:15,230
and then abandoning you,
your face wasn't full of hate,

301
00:13:15,230 --> 00:13:17,270
you were smiling as if
you were telling a joke

302
00:13:17,270 --> 00:13:20,090
that was amusing
only to you.

303
00:13:20,090 --> 00:13:22,030
And then
I understood.

304
00:13:22,030 --> 00:13:24,070
You don't want
to kill Shishio.

305
00:13:24,070 --> 00:13:26,100
In fact, you'd
be scared to try,

306
00:13:26,100 --> 00:13:29,030
because you know that after
your experience in the forest,

307
00:13:29,030 --> 00:13:31,230
when Shishio himself was
betrayed and was badly burned,

308
00:13:31,230 --> 00:13:33,280
he was even closer
to death than you were

309
00:13:33,280 --> 00:13:35,280
and the power he
developed as a result

310
00:13:35,280 --> 00:13:37,270
is much stronger than yours.

311
00:13:37,270 --> 00:13:39,260
So, when you joined
the Juupongatana,

312
00:13:39,260 --> 00:13:41,150
you did so only
on the condition

313
00:13:41,150 --> 00:13:42,210
that you could
attack Shishio

314
00:13:42,210 --> 00:13:44,100
and try to kill
him at anytime.

315
00:13:44,100 --> 00:13:45,280
Now, why would
you insist on that

316
00:13:45,280 --> 00:13:48,040
if you never really
intended to try?

317
00:13:48,040 --> 00:13:49,100
I'll tell you why.

318
00:13:49,100 --> 00:13:51,210
As long as everyone knew about
your agreement with Shishio,

319
00:13:51,210 --> 00:13:54,180
it would appear that Shishio had
to be on guard against you,

320
00:13:54,180 --> 00:13:56,250
which would make it appear
that he was afraid of you,

321
00:13:56,250 --> 00:14:00,030
and if people thought he was
afraid then they would be too.

322
00:14:00,030 --> 00:14:01,220
You live off
other people's fear.

323
00:14:01,220 --> 00:14:03,110
It feeds you,
nourishes you.

324
00:14:03,110 --> 00:14:05,280
It's the only thing that gives
meaning to your miserable life.

325
00:14:05,280 --> 00:14:08,170
So, killing Shishio is the
last thing you'd want to do,

326
00:14:08,170 --> 00:14:10,250
cause he's a lot more useful
to you alive than dead.

327
00:14:10,250 --> 00:14:14,050
♪

328
00:14:14,050 --> 00:14:15,280
I could be wrong on
some of the details,

329
00:14:15,280 --> 00:14:17,240
but generally, I'm
pretty close to the truth.

330
00:14:17,240 --> 00:14:19,250
♪

331
00:14:19,250 --> 00:14:21,100
(snickers)

332
00:14:21,100 --> 00:14:25,120
♪

333
00:14:25,120 --> 00:14:29,260
(both chuckling)

334
00:14:29,260 --> 00:14:34,080
♪

335
00:14:34,080 --> 00:14:37,290
(both laughing loudly)

336
00:14:39,070 --> 00:14:41,070
Go on, laugh all you like!

337
00:14:41,070 --> 00:14:44,070
Let's see if you're still
laughing a few moments from now,

338
00:14:44,070 --> 00:14:46,180
after I've slashed
you to pieces.

339
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:53,200
Are you ready?

340
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:55,210
Are you ready
to die, Saito?

341
00:14:55,210 --> 00:14:58,260
♪

342
00:14:58,260 --> 00:15:00,140
Come on.

343
00:15:00,140 --> 00:15:02,090
Enough talk, I want
to get this over with

344
00:15:02,090 --> 00:15:03,120
as quickly as possible.

345
00:15:03,120 --> 00:15:05,090
I've got work
to do, come on!

346
00:15:05,090 --> 00:15:06,090
Bastard!

347
00:15:06,090 --> 00:15:07,150
(growling)

348
00:15:07,150 --> 00:15:10,260
♪

349
00:15:10,260 --> 00:15:14,280
He thinks he can trick me by
using a tortoise shell shield.

350
00:15:14,280 --> 00:15:17,040
But that trick won't work
against the gatotsu.

351
00:15:17,040 --> 00:15:26,160
♪

352
00:15:26,160 --> 00:15:27,250
What the--?

353
00:15:27,250 --> 00:15:29,120
You see, it's no trick.

354
00:15:29,120 --> 00:15:31,160
The tortoise shell
is so perfectly round

355
00:15:31,160 --> 00:15:34,090
that it will deflect the
thrust of any weapon or blade.

356
00:15:34,090 --> 00:15:36,160
It also prevents
you from seeing

357
00:15:36,160 --> 00:15:39,000
where my next thrust
is coming from.

358
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:40,090
(grunts)

359
00:15:40,090 --> 00:15:48,020
♪

360
00:15:48,020 --> 00:15:50,140
The tortoise shell technique
is actually very old.

361
00:15:50,140 --> 00:15:52,230
The first ones to use it
were ancestors of mine

362
00:15:52,230 --> 00:15:54,200
in Ryukyu hundreds
of years ago,

363
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:56,090
and I was the one
who rediscovered it.

364
00:15:56,090 --> 00:15:59,020
♪

365
00:15:59,020 --> 00:16:00,250
Your gatotsu
is useless now.

366
00:16:00,250 --> 00:16:01,290
And yet, you
have to use it

367
00:16:01,290 --> 00:16:03,180
even though you know
you can't possibly win,

368
00:16:03,180 --> 00:16:05,130
because you have
no alternative.

369
00:16:05,130 --> 00:16:06,190
(snickering)

370
00:16:06,190 --> 00:16:07,260
I thank you, Saito,

371
00:16:07,260 --> 00:16:10,280
for providing such
delightful entertainment.

372
00:16:10,280 --> 00:16:14,070
(chuckling)

373
00:16:14,070 --> 00:16:16,190
Oh dear, you've
grown impatient.

374
00:16:16,190 --> 00:16:18,290
Very well, what
are you waiting for?

375
00:16:18,290 --> 00:16:26,150
♪

376
00:16:26,150 --> 00:16:29,090
(groans)

377
00:16:29,090 --> 00:16:31,250
We both know how
this is going to end.

378
00:16:31,250 --> 00:16:34,120
But I'll make it last
just as long as I can.

379
00:16:34,120 --> 00:16:36,120
You're the only one who's
ever figured out the way

380
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:40,160
I've used Shishio and those
fools in the Juupongatana group.

381
00:16:40,160 --> 00:16:41,160
But that's all right,

382
00:16:41,160 --> 00:16:45,120
since you're never going
to be telling anyone.

383
00:16:45,120 --> 00:16:47,250
You've been taking out your
frustration on everyone else

384
00:16:47,250 --> 00:16:49,240
over not being able
to kill Shishio.

385
00:16:49,240 --> 00:16:51,180
I can see that in
your twisted mind,

386
00:16:51,180 --> 00:16:53,290
each of the men you kill
is actually Shishio.

387
00:16:53,290 --> 00:16:56,160
Do you really think
that Shishio doesn't know?

388
00:16:56,160 --> 00:16:57,250
He's not stupid, you know.

389
00:16:57,250 --> 00:16:59,020
He may be deranged,

390
00:16:59,020 --> 00:17:01,260
but he's also a very
good judge of character.

391
00:17:01,260 --> 00:17:03,290
I'm sure he sees
right through you.

392
00:17:03,290 --> 00:17:05,060
What's ironic is
that you thought

393
00:17:05,060 --> 00:17:07,190
you were controlling
him, but in reality,

394
00:17:07,190 --> 00:17:09,050
he's used you like
a puppet to get you

395
00:17:09,050 --> 00:17:13,070
exactly where he
wants you to end up.

396
00:17:13,070 --> 00:17:15,250
I guess you really
are blind, aren't you?

397
00:17:15,250 --> 00:17:17,000
You go to hell!

398
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:21,290
♪

399
00:17:21,290 --> 00:17:24,020
Now, you fool, you
are the one who's blind,

400
00:17:24,020 --> 00:17:27,130
and at this close range,
your gotatsu is useless.

401
00:17:27,130 --> 00:17:28,220
Ah-ha, your
heart is racing.

402
00:17:28,220 --> 00:17:30,160
You're afraid,
aren't you?

403
00:17:30,160 --> 00:17:33,000
Because you know that
nothing can save you now.

404
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:35,230
(snickering)

405
00:17:35,230 --> 00:17:38,170
The killing blow will
come from behind my shield.

406
00:17:38,170 --> 00:17:41,260
Slide through your
ribs and into your heart,

407
00:17:41,260 --> 00:17:43,210
but where will
it come from?

408
00:17:43,210 --> 00:17:46,130
Top, bottom,
left, or right?

409
00:17:46,130 --> 00:17:47,220
If you had true
eyes of the heart,

410
00:17:47,220 --> 00:17:51,110
you would know,
but you don't, do you?

411
00:17:51,110 --> 00:17:53,010
Huh?

412
00:17:53,010 --> 00:17:55,180
(groaning)

413
00:18:08,040 --> 00:18:10,240
(screaming)

414
00:18:13,030 --> 00:18:14,190
How did...

415
00:18:14,190 --> 00:18:18,120
you do that, Saito?

416
00:18:18,120 --> 00:18:21,060
There are several kinds
of gatotsu attacks.

417
00:18:21,060 --> 00:18:23,280
Ishiki, the frontal attack
is the first position.

418
00:18:23,280 --> 00:18:26,210
Nishiki from above,
is the second position.

419
00:18:26,210 --> 00:18:29,220
Sanshiki, the mid-air
strike is the third.

420
00:18:29,220 --> 00:18:32,060
The attack I just used,
the zeroshiki position,

421
00:18:32,060 --> 00:18:33,210
is called
the hidden strike

422
00:18:33,210 --> 00:18:36,170
and you're the first one
I've used it against.

423
00:18:36,170 --> 00:18:38,200
I was saving that
honor for Battosai,

424
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:40,150
but I was forced
to change my mind.

425
00:18:40,150 --> 00:18:43,060
Lucky you,
congratulations.

426
00:18:43,060 --> 00:18:45,280
Now, I won't ever
take my revenge

427
00:18:45,280 --> 00:18:48,160
for what Shishio did.

428
00:18:48,160 --> 00:18:50,020
Poor Usui.

429
00:18:50,020 --> 00:18:52,190
You're so full of hate that
you still don't understand.

430
00:18:52,190 --> 00:18:54,220
You never had a
chance against Shishio.

431
00:18:54,220 --> 00:18:56,110
You were given
a marvelous gift,

432
00:18:56,110 --> 00:18:58,160
the eyes of the heart,
and all you did

433
00:18:58,160 --> 00:19:00,050
was use that gift
to lead a life

434
00:19:00,050 --> 00:19:02,270
filled with
hate and deceit.

435
00:19:02,270 --> 00:19:05,170
I've lived a life of
commitment and dedication

436
00:19:05,170 --> 00:19:08,110
to a goal and
I never gave up.

437
00:19:08,110 --> 00:19:10,120
Pity that what you
dedicated yourself to was

438
00:19:10,120 --> 00:19:12,260
a complete waste of time.

439
00:19:12,260 --> 00:19:15,030
Just because you were
able to defeat me,

440
00:19:15,030 --> 00:19:16,280
doesn't give you
the right to judge me.

441
00:19:16,280 --> 00:19:19,080
I have lived my life
by a simple credo :

442
00:19:19,080 --> 00:19:22,150
Do unto others as
they would do unto you.

443
00:19:22,150 --> 00:19:26,070
It was a difficult life, but
matters of honor often are.

444
00:19:26,070 --> 00:19:29,120
I wonder how long you will
stay loyal to your credo

445
00:19:29,120 --> 00:19:32,110
like I was to mine.

446
00:19:32,110 --> 00:19:33,260
(groans)

447
00:19:38,240 --> 00:19:39,260
How long?

448
00:19:39,260 --> 00:19:41,160
Till I die.

449
00:19:41,160 --> 00:19:50,180
♪

450
00:19:50,180 --> 00:19:52,090
Kenshin Himura was right.

451
00:19:52,090 --> 00:19:53,290
The Juupongatana have come.

452
00:19:53,290 --> 00:19:55,120
Okina's not strong
enough to fight,

453
00:19:55,120 --> 00:19:57,120
which means there's
only seven of us.

454
00:19:57,120 --> 00:19:59,100
So, we're facing
a real tough job,

455
00:19:59,100 --> 00:20:01,130
but we can do it
if we all work together.

456
00:20:01,130 --> 00:20:02,140
All right!

457
00:20:02,140 --> 00:20:04,070
What do you know,
it finally sounds to me

458
00:20:04,070 --> 00:20:05,230
like we're gonna have
a little fun this time.

459
00:20:05,230 --> 00:20:06,290
You call it fun, huh?

460
00:20:06,290 --> 00:20:09,280
Well, I got news for you,
there are 140 of them.

461
00:20:09,280 --> 00:20:12,010
So, the odds are 20
to one in their favor.

462
00:20:12,010 --> 00:20:13,230
You've got it
all wrong, kid.

463
00:20:13,230 --> 00:20:18,060
These guys are here just
to keep you from running away.

464
00:20:18,060 --> 00:20:21,070
The only fighting you gotta do
is against the three of us.

465
00:20:21,070 --> 00:20:25,220
Just myself and two others,
Henya and Iwanbo.

466
00:20:25,220 --> 00:20:26,280
Well, what are
you waiting for?

467
00:20:26,280 --> 00:20:28,150
Come on out!

468
00:20:28,150 --> 00:20:31,130
I can't cut your heads
off if you're in there!

469
00:20:31,130 --> 00:20:34,270
And I want each of your heads
as a gift for Mr. Shishio.

470
00:20:34,270 --> 00:20:36,070
With a gift like
that, he just might,

471
00:20:36,070 --> 00:20:38,130
well, you know, ask me to--
know what I mean.

472
00:20:38,130 --> 00:20:41,090
That nutcase is a member
of the Juupongatana?

473
00:20:41,090 --> 00:20:43,100
I guess so.

474
00:20:43,100 --> 00:20:45,040
What should we do?

475
00:20:45,040 --> 00:20:46,070
Well, seven
against three

476
00:20:46,070 --> 00:20:48,190
is a lot better than
seven against 140.

477
00:20:48,190 --> 00:20:49,200
Accept the challenge.

478
00:20:49,200 --> 00:20:51,240
What other choice have you?

479
00:20:51,240 --> 00:20:53,260
A plan of attack,
that's what we need.

480
00:20:53,260 --> 00:20:56,170
I think we should take the
offensive and attack them first.

481
00:20:56,170 --> 00:20:58,130
Yes, and we'll
coordinate our efforts

482
00:20:58,130 --> 00:21:01,090
based on which opponent
each of you is fighting.

483
00:21:01,090 --> 00:21:02,150
If you've won your fight

484
00:21:02,150 --> 00:21:04,170
and your opponent
is no longer dangerous,

485
00:21:04,170 --> 00:21:07,000
go and help someone
else who's in trouble.

486
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:10,150
Kaoru, Yoshi, you two take
the guy with the red hair.

487
00:21:10,150 --> 00:21:13,050
Misao, you take the woman with
the scythe, but be careful.

488
00:21:13,050 --> 00:21:14,250
She's dangerous.

489
00:21:14,250 --> 00:21:18,020
Shirojo, you and the others
take on that huge tub of lard.

490
00:21:18,020 --> 00:21:21,250
That stupid looking fellow with
the moronic grin on his face.

491
00:21:21,250 --> 00:21:22,250
Huh?

492
00:21:22,250 --> 00:21:23,250
If we get through
the first stage

493
00:21:23,250 --> 00:21:25,260
of the attack
successfully, we'll regroup

494
00:21:25,260 --> 00:21:27,080
and decide on
our new strategy.

495
00:21:27,080 --> 00:21:28,220
Good luck.

496
00:21:28,220 --> 00:21:29,220
Right!

497
00:21:29,220 --> 00:21:30,250
♪

498
00:21:30,250 --> 00:21:31,270
Let's go everyone!

499
00:21:31,270 --> 00:21:33,290
♪

500
00:21:33,290 --> 00:21:35,140
(shouting)

501
00:21:35,140 --> 00:21:46,050
♪

502
00:21:46,050 --> 00:21:47,050
I thought you
said the room

503
00:21:47,050 --> 00:21:48,150
where we were gonna
fight the next duel

504
00:21:48,150 --> 00:21:49,200
was just down the hall.

505
00:21:49,200 --> 00:21:52,030
I can't go on carrying you
like this forever, you know.

506
00:21:52,030 --> 00:21:55,100
The swordsman that's waiting is
the best in the Juupongatana.

507
00:21:55,100 --> 00:21:56,290
Though he looks like a kid.

508
00:21:56,290 --> 00:21:58,110
She must mean
Sojiro Seta.

509
00:21:58,110 --> 00:22:01,190
♪

510
00:22:05,010 --> 00:22:07,130
Huh?

511
00:22:07,130 --> 00:22:09,000
What'd you stop for,
come on!

512
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:10,040
That's Hoji's library.

513
00:22:10,040 --> 00:22:11,230
It hasn't been
used for a long time.

514
00:22:11,230 --> 00:22:12,270
It's vacant.

515
00:22:12,270 --> 00:22:15,110
Kenshin, we are
short on time, remember?

516
00:22:15,110 --> 00:22:16,100
Hey!

517
00:22:20,190 --> 00:22:21,190
He's here.

518
00:22:21,190 --> 00:22:23,080
I told you that's
not the right room.

519
00:22:23,080 --> 00:22:25,250
There's no one there.

520
00:22:25,250 --> 00:22:33,060
♪

521
00:22:33,060 --> 00:22:35,050
There is someone there.

